\begin_layout Plain Layout
An integral of time-weighted square-error cost function was used to penalize later tracking errors more than transient ones:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
J=\intop^{t_{f}}_{0}\left(q_{e}\cdot t\left\Vert e\left(t\right)\right\Vert ^{2}+r_{u}\left\Vert u\left(t\right)\right\Vert ^{2}\right)dt+W_{\text{fail}}\left(t_{\text{fail}}-t\right)^{2},
\]

\end_inset

where 
\begin_inset Formula $r_{u}=0.2$
\end_inset

,
 
\begin_inset Formula $q_{e}=1$
\end_inset

,
 
\begin_inset Formula $W_{\text{fail}}=1000$
\end_inset

,
 
\begin_inset Formula $t_{f}\in\mathbb{R}_{>t_{0}}$
\end_inset

 is the total simulation duration,
 and 
\begin_inset Formula $t_{\text{fail}}\in\left(t_{0},t_{f}\right)$
\end_inset

 is time at which the drone escapes the simulated space (
\begin_inset Formula $t_{f}=t_{\text{fail}}$
\end_inset

 if it does not escape).
 The integral was evaluated using the trapezoidal rule.
